<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 06 at 6:15PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central Marion
and central Webster Counties through 645 PM EDT...
At 615 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Friendship, or near
Preston, moving northwest at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Preston, Church Hill, Dumas and Draneville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
